ent about the extraordinary gratuity of existence, and the remarkable ways in which such wonderment has been expressed. Against the grain of such widespread developments Grace and Philosophy proposes a perspective that maintains a place of importance in philosophy for such wonder and for the many forms in which it has manifested itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGrace (Aesthetics). 0aGrace (Theology). 0aLife. 0aPhilosophy and religion. 0aPhilosophy. 0aSufficient reason. 0aWonder (Philosophy). 0aWonder. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Epistemology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311127268908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019z978311127498040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077355763540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773557635423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773557635/original  a978-3-11-127268-9  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-127498-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles